---
import ElevationLayout from '../../layouts/ElevationLayout.astro';

const structuredData = {
  "@type": "SoftwareApplication",
  "name": "The Kitchen Table",
  "description": "A family meal-planning app from Evoked. No streaks, no scores, no surveillance. Heritage recipes welcomed as fragments. COPPA-compliant by design. iOS beta on TestFlight.",
  "applicationCategory": "LifestyleApplication",
  "operatingSystem": "iOS",
  "creator": { "@id": "https://evoked.dev/#person" },
  "publisher": { "@id": "https://evoked.dev/#organization" }
};
---

{/*
  Voice register: intimate-domestic, threshold-not-yet-crossed sub-register.
  Per evoked-dev/CLAUDE.md "Voice Discipline Scope" addendum (Hoshi, 2026-05-03):
  em-dashes are permitted on intimate-domestic surfaces - the dash signals breath,
  hesitation, gentleness. The em-dashes below are register-correct, not voice-tells
  failures. The founder-public voice-tells-audit.sh ruleset does not apply to this
  file. If a future reviewer in founder-public discipline-mode reads this page and
  reflexively flags the em-dashes, read the addendum first.

  Chrome: J register (parchment + brass + sigil + astrolabe) extracted from
  /elevation/j.html via ElevationLayout. Body typography is sentence-case serif
  italic, not the UPPERCASE Syncopate of founder-public Hero/Section. This is the
  designed seam Hoshi named - one product, two registers, both correct on their
  own surfaces.
*/}

<ElevationLayout
  title="The Kitchen Table"
  description="A family meal-planning app from Evoked. No streaks, no scores, no surveillance. Heritage recipes welcomed as fragments. COPPA-compliant by design. iOS beta on TestFlight."
  structuredData={structuredData}
>
  <article class="kt">
    <header class="kt-hero">
      <p class="kt-eyebrow">From Evoked · A family meal-planning app</p>
      <h1 class="kt-title">The Kitchen Table</h1>
      <p class="kt-tagline">Family flourishing through food.</p>
      <p class="kt-sub">A quiet meal-planning app for families. iOS beta on TestFlight.</p>
    </header>

    <section class="kt-section">
      <h2>What this is</h2>
      <p>
        We made it because we couldn't find a meal-planning app we trusted to leave
        open in a kitchen where children can see the screen.
      </p>
      <p>
        Food is never just food. The moment you ask a family <em>what do you eat?</em>
        you're asking about identity, culture, memory, survival.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Kitchen Table is built to honor that &mdash; not to optimize your diet or
        gamify your groceries, but to help families plan meals, preserve heritage
        recipes, and eat together.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="kt-section">
      <h2>Who's at the table</h2>
      <p>
        Table keepers, planners, members, learners, guests. Everyone has a place.
        Everyone participates according to their capacity.
      </p>
      <p>
        A four-year-old can be at the table. A grandparent who only remembers
        "some kind of dumpling" can be at the table. A teenager who wants quiet
        can be at the table without performing.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="kt-section">
      <h2>What we honor</h2>
      <ul class="kt-principles">
        <li>
          <strong>Reverent references, not reductive captures.</strong>
          A recipe is a doorway, not a database row.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Fragments are sacred.</strong>
          A single memory is enough. A story without measurements is complete.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Family defines family.</strong>
          Your words for who you are. Not our taxonomy.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>The system knows when to be quiet.</strong>
          Grief, busy seasons, days that are simply hard. We step back.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Space for all of it.</strong>
          Celebration and grief. Roots and searching. Heritage embraced and
          heritage reclaimed.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="kt-aside">
        If a family only remembers "some kind of dumpling" from a grandmother lost
        to displacement, that fragment is welcome here. We don't require
        completeness. We honor what remains.
      </p>
      <p class="kt-closing">
        Some recipes survive because someone made sure they would.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="kt-section">
      <h2>What this is not</h2>
      <p>No streaks. No scores. No leaderboards.</p>
      <p>
        No notifications designed to pull you back when you didn't choose to come
        back. No engagement metrics that override how you're actually feeling. No
        quiet collection of behavioral data we'd rather you not think about.
      </p>
      <p>
        No advertising. Ever. Not now, not when we're bigger, not when someone
        offers us money to start.
      </p>
      <p>
        Children's profiles are unreachable to anyone outside the family &mdash;
        by architecture, not by promise. COPPA-compliant by design, not by retrofit.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="kt-section kt-section--waitlist">
      <h2>Join the waitlist</h2>
      <p class="kt-waitlist-blurb">
        We'll write when there's something real to share. Not before.
      </p>
      <form id="kt-waitlist-form" class="kt-waitlist-form" novalidate>
        <label class="kt-waitlist-label" for="kt-waitlist-email">Email</label>
        <div class="kt-waitlist-row">
          <input
            type="email"
            id="kt-waitlist-email"
            name="email"
            placeholder="your.email@example.com"
            required
            aria-label="Email address"
          />
          <input
            type="text"
            name="website"
            class="kt-hp-field"
            tabindex="-1"
            autocomplete="off"
            aria-hidden="true"
          />
          <button type="submit">Join waitlist</button>
        </div>
      </form>
      <p id="kt-waitlist-status" class="kt-waitlist-status hidden" aria-live="polite"></p>
      <p class="kt-form-note">
        No spam. No selling. Just one email when we open the door wider.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</ElevationLayout>

<script>
  function attachKitchenTableWaitlist() {
    const form = document.getElementById('kt-waitlist-form') as HTMLFormElement | null;
    if (!form || form.dataset.wired === 'true') return;
    form.dataset.wired = 'true';

    const emailInput = document.getElementById('kt-waitlist-email') as HTMLInputElement;
    const status = document.getElementById('kt-waitlist-status') as HTMLParagraphElement;
    const button = form.querySelector('button') as HTMLButtonElement;
    const hpInput = form.querySelector<HTMLInputElement>('input[name="website"]');

    const showError = (msg: string) => {
      button.disabled = false;
      button.textContent = 'Join waitlist';
      status.textContent = msg;
      status.classList.remove('hidden', 'success');
      status.classList.add('error');
    };

    form.addEventListener('submit', async (e) => {
      e.preventDefault();
      const email = emailInput.value.trim();
      if (!email) return;

      // Honeypot: bot filled the hidden field - silent success
      if (hpInput?.value) {
        button.textContent = 'Thank you ✓';
        emailInput.value = '';
        return;
      }

      button.disabled = true;
      button.textContent = 'Joining...';
      status.textContent = '';
      status.classList.remove('error', 'success', 'hidden');

      try {
        // 1. Fetch challenge token (HMAC-signed by server)
        const cRes = await fetch('/api/newsletter/challenge');
        if (!cRes.ok) {
          showError('Something went wrong. Try again.');
          return;
        }
        const { token, ts } = await cRes.json();

        // 2. Submit with token + honeypot
        const sRes = await fetch('/api/newsletter/subscribe', {
          method: 'POST',
          headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
          body: JSON.stringify({ email, token, ts, hp: hpInput?.value || '' }),
        });

        if (sRes.ok) {
          button.textContent = 'Thank you ✓';
          emailInput.value = '';
          status.textContent = 'You are in. Welcome.';
          status.classList.remove('error', 'hidden');
          status.classList.add('success');
        } else {
          const data = await sRes.json().catch(() => ({} as { error?: string }));
          showError(data?.error || 'Something went wrong. Try again.');
        }
      } catch {
        showError('Something went wrong. Try again.');
      }
    });
  }
  attachKitchenTableWaitlist();
  document.addEventListener('astro:after-swap', attachKitchenTableWaitlist);
</script>

<style>
  /* ---------------------------------------------------------------
     Kitchen Table - intimate-domestic body inside J register chrome.
     Typography is sentence-case serif italic, slower rhythm, softer
     accents than the founder-public Hero/Section components.
     ---------------------------------------------------------------*/
  .kt {
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: clamp(2rem, 1.5rem + 3vw, 5rem) var(--el-content-pad)
            clamp(3rem, 2rem + 4vw, 6rem);
    color: var(--el-text);
    font-family: var(--el-body);
  }

  .kt-hero {
    text-align: left;
    margin-bottom: clamp(3rem, 2rem + 3vw, 5rem);
  }
  .kt-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--el-ui);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--el-accent);
    margin: 0 0 clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 1vw, 2rem);
  }
  .kt-title {
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 1.8rem + 3.5vw, 4.5rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    color: var(--el-text);
  }
  .kt-tagline {
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 1.05rem + 0.8vw, 1.6rem);
    line-height: 1.4;
    color: var(--el-text);
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
    max-width: 28ch;
  }
  .kt-sub {
    font-family: var(--el-ui);
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--el-text-quiet);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .kt-section {
    margin: clamp(3rem, 2rem + 2.5vw, 4.5rem) 0;
    padding-top: clamp(2rem, 1.5rem + 1.5vw, 3rem);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
  }
  .kt-section h2 {
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 1.25rem + 1vw, 2rem);
    line-height: 1.25;
    color: var(--el-text);
    margin: 0 0 clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 0.75vw, 1.75rem);
    text-transform: none;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }
  .kt-section p {
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1rem + 0.25vw, 1.2rem);
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--el-text-soft);
    margin: 0 0 1.1rem;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }
  .kt-section p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .kt-section em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--el-text);
  }

  .kt-principles {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .kt-principles li {
    padding: 1.1rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1rem + 0.25vw, 1.15rem);
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--el-text-soft);
  }
  .kt-principles li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .kt-principles strong {
    display: block;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--el-text);
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .kt-aside {
    margin-top: clamp(1.5rem, 1rem + 1vw, 2.25rem) !important;
    padding: 1rem 0 1rem 1.25rem;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--el-accent);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--el-text-soft);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }
  .kt-closing {
    margin-top: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 0.75vw, 1.75rem) !important;
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 1.05rem + 0.5vw, 1.4rem);
    color: var(--el-text);
  }

  /* ---- Waitlist ---- */
  .kt-section--waitlist { text-align: left; }
  .kt-waitlist-blurb {
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1rem + 0.25vw, 1.2rem);
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--el-text-soft);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
    max-width: 50ch;
  }
  .kt-waitlist-label {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--el-ui);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--el-text-quiet);
    margin-bottom: 0.55rem;
  }
  .kt-waitlist-form {
    max-width: 480px;
  }
  .kt-waitlist-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--el-text);
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .kt-waitlist-row input[type="email"] {
    flex: 1;
    padding: 0.45rem 0;
    background: transparent;
    border: none;
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 0.95rem + 0.2vw, 1.1rem);
    color: var(--el-text);
    min-width: 0;
  }
  .kt-waitlist-row input[type="email"]::placeholder {
    color: var(--el-text-quiet);
  }
  .kt-waitlist-row input[type="email"]:focus { outline: none; }
  .kt-waitlist-row button {
    padding: 0.45rem 0;
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--el-accent);
    border: none;
    font-family: var(--el-ui);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 13px;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    cursor: pointer;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .kt-waitlist-row button:hover { color: var(--el-text); }
  .kt-waitlist-row button:disabled { opacity: 0.6; cursor: wait; }

  /* honeypot - visually + semantically hidden but submittable */
  .kt-hp-field {
    position: absolute;
    left: -9999px;
    top: -9999px;
    opacity: 0;
    height: 0;
    width: 0;
    z-index: -1;
  }

  .kt-waitlist-status {
    font-family: var(--el-ui);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-top: 0.85rem;
    min-height: 1.2em;
    color: var(--el-text-quiet);
  }
  .kt-waitlist-status.hidden { display: none; }
  .kt-waitlist-status.success { color: var(--el-accent); }
  .kt-waitlist-status.error { color: #c44; }

  .kt-form-note {
    font-family: var(--el-ui);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--el-text-quiet);
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  /* Mobile fine-tune: keep the waitlist row inline; only wrap when truly cramped */
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .kt-waitlist-row {
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }
    .kt-waitlist-row button {
      padding-top: 0.85rem;
    }
  }
</style>
